  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Step by Step-Promoting Peace, Freedom of Expression and Press Freedom in South Sudan.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is design to facilitate citizens&#x2019; interaction and freedom to engage with their leaders and communities in the implementation of the revitalized peace agreement process and other national agendas that will promote   peace-building in South Sudan. The radio programs will be aimed to provide free platform for discussions on peace-building, democratic processes, good governance, Justice, trauma healing and reconciliation that will intend to enhance freedom of expression and press freedom in South Sudan. 
The project will build on the work of an earlier project that was funded through CTP &#x2018;&#x2019;No Peace, Without Democracy and No Democracy without Freedom of Expression in South Sudan&#x2019;&#x2019;. The project aims to create an enabling environment for journalists and citizens to express themselves freely. The activities will be interactive radio talk shows, community dialogues and radio dramas that will focus on the revitalized peace agreement and its supplement provided in Chapter 1, 2, 3 and 5 of ARCISS i.e. Justice, forgiveness, trauma healing and reconciliation.</narrative>
  </description>
